  "prompt": "Where can you find some build examples for Titan Quest?",
  "response": "Finding good Titan Quest build examples can be a bit tricky, as the game's community isn't as large as some other ARPGs. However, here are some of the best resources and strategies for finding build examples:\n\n**1. Grim Dawn Forums (Related, but Highly Useful):**\n\n*   **Why Grim Dawn?** Titan Quest shares a lot of mechanics with Grim Dawn, a spiritual successor made by the same developers. Many Grim Dawn builds are adaptable to Titan Quest, especially if you understand the underlying principles. The mastery skills are quite similar.\n*   **Search Strategies:** Look for builds focused on:\n    *   **Specific Damage Types:**  Physical, Pierce, Bleeding, Vitality, Aether, Chaos, Fire, Cold, Lightning, Poison. Figure out which damage type appeals to you.\n    *   **Specific Masteries/Classes:** Figure out two Masteries you are interested in.  Many builds will mention a Masteries name (e.g. \"Warden,\" \"Elementalist,\" etc.) Find the equivalent masteries in Titan Quest and look at the core skills it relies on.\n    *   **Specific Skills:** Skills often have very similar functions. Figure out what skills in Grim Dawn are similar to the skills you want to use in Titan Quest.\n\n**2. Titan Quest Forums and Fan Sites (Best for Direct TQ Info):**\n\n*   **Steam Community Forums:** The Steam forums for Titan Quest Anniversary Edition often have build discussions and guides.  Use the search function to look for builds related to specific masteries or playstyles.\n*   **Unofficial Forums:**  Search for \"Titan Quest Forums\" on Google.  Older forums may still have valuable information archived, even if they are no longer actively maintained.\n*   **Fan Sites (Use with Caution):** Some older fan sites still exist, but their information may be outdated or incomplete.\n\n**3. YouTube:**\n\n*   **Search Terms:** Use very specific search terms like:\n    *   \"Titan Quest Anniversary Edition [Mastery 1] [Mastery 2] Build\" (e.g., \"Titan Quest Anniversary Edition Warfare Dream Build\")\n    *   \"Titan Quest Ragnarok [Specific Playstyle] Build\" (e.g., \"Titan Quest Ragnarok Pet Build\")\n    *   \"Titan Quest [Damage Type] Build Guide\" (e.g., \"Titan Quest Lightning Build Guide\")\n*   **Evaluate Critically:** Not all YouTube builds are created equal. Look for videos that:\n    *   Explain *why* the build works, not just *what* to do.\n    *   Show gameplay of the build in action, preferably on a higher difficulty.\n    *   Offer alternative gear choices.\n    *   Have recent upload dates (if possible, to ensure the information is still relevant).\n\n**4. Build Simulators/Calculators:**\n\n*   **tqcalc.com:** A very useful site for planning and sharing builds.\n*   **Benefits:**\n    *   Allows you to allocate skill points and attributes virtually.\n    *   You can save and share build links with others.\n    *   Helps you experiment with different mastery combinations.\n\n**Tips for Adapting Builds:**\n\n*   **Understand the Core Concepts:** Don't just blindly copy a build.  Understand the core mechanics that make it work. What damage type is it focused on? What are the key skills? How does it survive?\n*   **Gear is Important, But Not Everything:**  While specific gear can greatly enhance a build, focus on the *affixes* (bonuses) on the gear.  Look for affixes that boost your primary damage type, resistances, attribute points, and skill bonuses.  Use the best gear you can find with the desired affixes.\n*   **Don't Be Afraid to Experiment:**  The best way to learn is to try things out.  Respecs are relatively easy to do, so don't be afraid to experiment with different skills and gear combinations.\n*   **Consider Difficulty:** A build that works well on Normal might struggle on Epic or Legendary.  Adjust your build and gear as needed to compensate for the increased difficulty.\n*   **Focus on Resistances:**  Resistances are crucial for survival, especially on higher difficulties.  Prioritize gear and skills that provide resistances to different damage types.\n\n**General Build Archetypes (Things to Think About):**\n\n*   **Melee:** Close-range combat, often relying on high damage and survivability.\n*   **Ranged:** Long-range combat, often relying on high damage output from a safe distance.\n*   **Caster:** Relies on spells and skills for damage.\n*   **Summoner/Pet Build:** Uses pets to deal damage and tank for the player.\n*   **Hybrid:** Combines elements of different archetypes.\n\nBy using these resources and tips, you should be able to find or adapt build examples that suit your playstyle in Titan Quest. Good luck!\n",
